"""
cnn_model.py  –  CNN training and evaluation for AID image dataset
==================================================================
Trains a temporal EfficientNet-B0 on the CARLA-rendered highway camera images
produced by carla_capture.py.

Architecture
------------
  - EfficientNet-B0 backbone (ImageNet pretrained, torchvision)
  - N frames uniformly sampled from each 60-frame (30s) sliding window
  - Per-frame features (1280-d) averaged → temporal context vector
  - MLP classification head: 1280 → 256 → 1 (binary)
  - Two training phases:
      Phase 1  – backbone frozen, head trained (fast convergence)
      Phase 2  – last 2 MBConv blocks + head fine-tuned at lr/10

Split alignment with SUMO Random Forest model
----------------------------------------------
  The SUMO macro-data split (train/val/test .h5) partitioned by scenario_id.
  This script reads those same scenario_id sets and applies them to the image
  metadata CSV so BOTH models are evaluated on exactly the same scenarios.
  No scenario windows can leak across splits.

Sliding window dataset
-----------------------
  - Window size  : 60 frames = 30 seconds at 2 FPS
  - Stride       : 3 frames (1.5 seconds shift per sample)
  - Frames/window: 8 frames sampled uniformly from each 60-frame window
                   (reduces GPU memory; 8 frames still covers the full 30s)
  - Label        : label of the LAST frame in the window
                   (predicts current state given 30s of history)

GPU notes (GTX 1060 3GB)
-------------------------
  - Images resized to 224×224 (EfficientNet-B0 native resolution)
  - batch_size = 6 sequences × 8 frames = 48 CNN forward passes per step
  - Backbone frozen in phase 1 → no activation storage → ~500 MB peak
  - Fine-tuning phase 2 with gradient checkpointing to stay under 3 GB
  - Falls back to CPU automatically if CUDA OOM

Usage
-----
  python cnn_model.py                    # full training pipeline
  python cnn_model.py --phase1-only      # freeze backbone only (fast, ~1h)
  python cnn_model.py --evaluate-only    # load saved model, run test set
  python cnn_model.py --hp-search        # try all hyperparameter combinations
"""

